Organization = {IEEE},
Abstract = {A new approach for solving an optimal control problem of ball pitching
   with an underactuated human-like robot arm is proposed. The system
   dynamics is simplified to a planar two-link robot with actuation only at
   the shoulder joint and a passive spring at the elbow joint representing
   the stiffness of the arm. The objective is to accelerate the ball from
   an initial configuration at rest in such a way that the projection of
   its velocity along a certain elevation angle is maximal at a predefined
   release line. The suggested procedure makes use of a parameterization of
   the robot motion in terms of geometric relations among the generalized
   coordinates. We systematically formulate a necessary condition for an
   optimal motion resulting in a nonlinear differential equation that
   describes a synchronization of the joint angles. A suitable solution is
   found by numerically searching over a finite number of free initial
   conditions.},
